{
  "description": "Crossover fixtures for the Irene<->bridge canonical-command contract: {utterance -> expected canonical command}. Producer half: Irene's TEST-18 suite asserts the captured command equals `expect`. Consumer half: the bridge's VWB-16 replays `expect` against its native layer. Authored by wb-mqtt-voice (TEST-18 Slice A); bound to the pinned catalog below — re-author bindings on re-pin if the guard test fails.",
  "catalog_version": "dbfd2855dac52026",
  "expect_kinds": {
    "actuate": "device-form command: POST /devices/{device_id}/canonical {capability, action, params}",
    "room-group": "room-form command (VWB-23): POST /rooms/{room_id}/canonical {group, action, scope}; scope auto = bare noun, all = the plural/«весь» signal",
    "read": "state read (ARCH-8 PR-5): GET /devices/{device_id}/state -> capability.field; `any_of` lists equally-correct targets",
    "clarify": "no command emitted: Irene asks a clarification naming the candidate devices"
  },
  "tiers": {
    "1": "green-able with the QUAL-35 T1 donation baseline (direct RU surfaces, noun lexicon, room aliases)",
    "2": "needs QUAL-35 T2 (numeric slot-filling with units, transliteration-tolerant CHOICE matching)"
  },
  "excluded_by_design": [
    "Cyrillic-spoken Latin names («ютуб», «эппл ти ви») — transliteration-tolerant matching is QUAL-35 T2; F41/F53 encode it and stay red until then",
    "light-subset pair nouns («ночники»/«тумбочки»/«полки») — dropped from v1; return as fixtures when the bridge adds compound devices for the pairs (needs a re-pin)",
    "power-group fan-out («выключи все розетки» as a room-group) — the bridge allow-lists fan-out to light+cover only; plugs/oven are reachable by NAME (see F04/F03), never by «свет»",
    "priority rules for same-room ambiguity — v1 clarifies (F20/F21); priorities are a later-release enhancement"
  ],
